info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 26 at 3:30AM MST until November 26 at 11:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM MST THIS MORNING... ...HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE SUNDAY NIGHT... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 50 MPH with gusts up to 75 MPH expected. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County including the Bordeaux Interchange along Interstate 25 between Chugwater and Wheatland. * WHEN...High Wind Warning remains valid until 11 AM MST this morning. High Wind Watch valid from 11 AM MST Sunday until 5 AM MST Monday. Winds will be strongest from late Sunday afternoon into early Monday morning. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight and high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
